      <lg xml:id="TolE0328">
<l>īmuṅ kammu murumeṉ kiḷaviyu</l>
<l>māmup peyaru mavaṟṟō raṉṉa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The words <foreign xml:lang="ta">īm</foreign> ' burial ground ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">kam</foreign> ' profession ' and <foreign xml:lang="ta">urum</foreign> ' thunder ',</l>
<l>these three nouns are of the same nature as those [verbal nouns].<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">īm</foreign> is sometimes glossed as <foreign xml:lang="ta">iṭukāṭu</foreign> ' burial ground ' ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">kam</foreign> as <foreign xml:lang="ta">kammiyaratu tolil</foreign> ' the profession of smiths ', and <foreign xml:lang="ta">urum</foreign> as <foreign xml:lang="ta">iṭi</foreign> ' thunder ' ;
          e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">kam + katitu &gt; kammukkaṭitu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
